  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Type: Bug\n\nSummary: There is a rule listed for mobile in https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/4910 :\nNotification appears whenever a message is received and the app is on background or turned off\nThe assumption is that the same behaviour is valid for desktop.\n\n**Expected behaviour**\n\nPush notifications should be received when app is closed on desktop\n\n**Actual behaviour**\n\nPush notifications are not received when app is closed on desktop\n\n**Reproduction**\n\n1. Open desktop app on device A\n2. Start 1-1 chat with a different user on device B\n3. Close Status app on device A\n4. Send a message from device B to device A\n\nAnd if expected behaviour is not to show the notification when desktop app is closed, \nshould it re-appear when app is opened again, or not show at all?\nThank you.",
